
26/04/05:  RELEASE 1.0.0 - BM

* no bug or RFE reported from previous release. toolwrap seems to work pretty well, so I raise
  version number to 1.0.0 (first "stable" release). 
* add parsing error message
* update documentation.

29/03/05:  RELEASE 0.2 - BM

* provide basename() fallback.
* fix some #ifdef's  
* fix manual page installation prefix
* fix command line options parsing (POSIXILY_CORRECT behaviour)
* fix install arguments (remove -C & -D switches)
* should compiles cleanly on Linux (x86, amd64, alpha), *BSD, Solaris, OS X

16/03/05:  RELEASE 0.1 - BM
	
* first toolwrap release for public use.

	
